{
  "text": "Pain is the most common complaint of trauma patients attending the emergency department (ED), with prevalence of 70% reported in the prehospital setting and 91% in EDs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, undertreatment of pain (oligoanalgesia) remains a widespread problem in the emergency setting [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Various reports have attributed oligoanalgesia to failure to assess/ underestimation of pain by healthcare workers [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] , lack of national/institutional guidelines for pain management [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] and limitations of currently available therapies [CITATION_13] .",
